      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The Labor Advocate in one of it's\nrecent issues has an article wherein\n1t discusses the labor question as it\nexists in the large cities of the\nUnited States. A brief mention is\nmade of Spokane. but 1t is such as\nto appeal to the sense of just pride\nof every labor organizer In the city.\nThe article states that Spokane is\none of the best organized cities in\nthe country and that although every\navenue of employment is under the\never watchful eye OF the alert union\ndelegate\" yet unjust demands are\nnever made and the labor bodies ever\nseem ready to submit their differ\nences to arbitration."
    }
  ]
